The '''application domain''' of a [[software]] system is the type of tasks for which the system is used or intended to be used.  This is closely related to a [[software engineering]] [[domain (software engineering)|domain]].

Examples of application domains are [[insurance]], [[computer-aided manufacturing]] and [[administration]].

See also ''[[CLR application domain]]'' - the runtime environment or an application within a process in the ''[[Common Language Runtime]] [[computing]]'' framework.